Time behaviour : The time that the system responds to the request.

>> It examines the ability of the system to respond to user inputs within a specified time and under specified conditions.

Ex : When we click on a button for examplw, what is the time that it takkes the system to act depending on our action.

Resources utilization : we might develop a very good application it on their mobile phones it uses a lot of memory or a lot of RAM. In this case usera will leave the application.

>> we need to make sure that the application is not consuming a huge amount of resources depending on its objective.

Capacity : If number of the user using the application at the same time then the capacity should be agoal of the project.

Types of performance testing

stress testing, scalability testing, spike testing, endurance testing, concurrency testing, capacity testing
